The sex, class are the more important follow by age and embarked and in the botom number or siblings aboard. This Say probability or survived = no 0.4, if he is male and if he is in middle or lower class and he is an adult his probability of died is 11% if he is male and if he is in middle or lower class and he is a child and he has 3 or more siblings aboard the Titanic his probability of died is 7% if he is male and if he is in middle or lower class and he is a child and he doesn’t has 3 or more siblings aboard the Titanic his probability of survived is 89% if he is male and if he isn’t middle or lower class his probability of died is 42% if she is a woman ans she is lower class and she embarked in Cherbourg or Southampton her probability of died is 39% if she is a woman ans she is lower class and she doesn’t embark in Cherbourg or Southampton her probability of survived is 73% if she is a woman ans she isn’t lower class her probability of survived is 96%

True positive 21 (no survived) True negative 37 (yes survived) False positive 4 (no survived) False negative 9 (yes survived)

81.69% accuracy

  add_predictions(titanic_fit_1, type = "class")

  select(survived, pred)

           estimate = pred)
